			<p>My husband loves stuff like this and, hey, he wears a construction helmet to work every day!</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s the pasta I&#8217;ve been making for myself since college: can of tuna (in oil, don&#8217;t drain), can of drained &amp; sliced black olives, and minced garlic and Italian Seasoning.  Saute until hot, toss with pasta of your choice, and sprinkle with grated Parm.  </p>
<p>I don&#8217;t know why I felt the need to post that, except some of you other moms might like to whip this up for yourself some day you don&#8217;t feel like eating the usual sandwich-over-the-sink lunch.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s delish, but I must warn you that it will make your kitchen, breath, and possibly your very flesh (depending on how much garlic you go for) very smelly for the rest of the afternoon.</p>
<p>I make a lot of pasta using whatever I have around, but I don&#8217;t think I&#8217;ve ever made basil cream sauce.  I&#8217;m going to try this out!</p>
