			<p>Ree your killing me here. This can also be made with a bechamel sauce. I know you know how to make a roux. Personally I use a sour cream addition and leave out the heavy cream.<br />
Also I use a mix of romano and reggiano cheeses.<br />
Recently I have become hooked on another summer pasta the cold one. Mixed short pasta of choice, some picked or chopped chicken rotissere or left over, olives, artichoke hearts, feta cheese, chopped onion, grape tomatoes and a nice vinaigrette. Toss and chill. It is great in this kind of heat.</p>
