<p>I made this pasta primavera tonight as a double barrelled &#8220;Hi neighbor, we&#8217;re new&#8221; and &#8220;congrats on your new baby&#8221; gift. We recently moved to a new neighborhood and have been SO busy we haven&#8217;t been able to introduce ourselves around &#8211; but it was hard to miss the heavily pregnant woman across the street.</p>
<p>Not knowing if they were vegetarian, etc., (Can&#8217;t be too careful on the East coast about this sort of thing, says the Texan) I thought this would be good for the nursing mother (lots of milk and calcium, uh huh, that&#8217;s right!) and fresh veggies while also being veggie safe.</p>
<p>I used protein plus penne, and had a little taste before dishing it up. YUMMO!</p>
<p>And it was a HUGE hit. Thanks for helping me make new friends <img src='http://static.thepioneerwoman.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif' alt=':)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
