			<h4>anna l'americana <span>On Sunday, June 1 at 8:41 am</span></h4>
			<p>Delicious.  A tip from an old hand at Italian food:  Add a ladleful of the starchy water from the cooking pasta to the sauce before you dump the pasta into it, it will help thicken the sauce (any sauce) a bit as it cooks.   Love the recipe &#8211; sauteing all the veggies gives a much better flavor than blanching.  The great thing about Primavera is that with different combinations (look at all the yummy variations posted here!) you can make it all the time and always have a different delicious dish just using whatever ingredients you have on hand.  BTW:  the Italian word for summer is &#8220;estate&#8221; pronounced &#8220;eh-staht-ey&#8221;.</p>
